						               													<description>An ingenious cross between Risk and Scrabble Junior. From the instructions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Worldmaster: A game of strategy for two or four players [in partnerships]. Build a CONNECTED EMPIRE, covering at least half the letters of each of its countries with letters of your colour -- Red or Blue. Numbered circles tell you how many letters you need to cover.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board consists of a Risk-like simplified map of the world. Countries are labelled like words on a Scrabble Junior board; each letter is enclosed in a box the size of a Scrabble tile. Each country also has a numbered circle indicating half the length of the country&amp;rsquo;s name (rounded up; two circles for countries whose names have an even number of letters). Each player (or partnership) receives a bag of letter tiles, which contains just enough to cover all the letters on the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;High-speed rules summary from the instructions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULE 1: In each turn place one or more letters, anywhere, or store up all of them. End the turn by drawing four, always.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULE 2: Earn country &amp;quot;flags&amp;quot; -- coloured markers -- once you&amp;rsquo;ve covered as many letters as the circles show. (Only one flag of your colour in any country! The enemy may share countries with two circles, if you don&amp;rsquo;t prevent this.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULE 3: Flags on EIGHT connected countries wins -- or ELEVEN in games with the Airports rule. (Two extra letters earn an &amp;quot;airport ring&amp;quot; over the flag. Groups connect by air when each group has an airport.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
